On Sat, Nov 27, 2004 at 12:10:24PM -0500, Casting Fool wrote:
> Sometimes the turn signals will stop working when I hit the brakes.  But I
> (finally) figured out that it's due to the battery (brand new) running down
> to the point where it can't support both the brake lights and the turn
> signals together.

If this is the case Mike, you have to investigate your charging
system. Battery is only a container for electrical power to provide
starting and some buffer ability. the real power for all your electric
devices come from the alternator.

